 As the president gets ready to address the nation this evening , The South African Liquor Brand owners Association wants to know what scientific reasoning is used by the government when imposing a booze ban. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Liquor Brand Owners Association wants the government to provide details on what scientific reasoning it uses when imposing a booze ban. The association said the Trade and Industry Department has confirmed that the National Coronavirus Command Council is intending on banning all alcohol sales starting from this Easter weekend. READ: Increase in excise tax risks job losses, says liquor association The Ministerial Advisory Committee also recommending stricter lockdown regulations from this weekend. There are fears the holidays could lead to a COVID-19 third wave.